contentrichtext.text: {{Orphan|date=February 2009}} {{For|the electronic toy|Furby}} '''Furby''', [[Sweden]] (< fura 'pine' + bua 'plĈace') is a locality in Badelunda [[parish]], [[Västerås Municipality]]. Furby was previously a parish of its own, but now only a church ruin remains. Furby is a few miles north of Lake [[Mälaren]] and situated east--near [[Anundshögen]] ([[:sv:Anundshögen|Swedish Wikipedia article]]), the [[ship]] [[burial mound]] of legendary [[King of Sweden|Swedish King]] [[Anund]]. == External links == In [[Swedish language|Swedish]]: *[http://hem.passagen.se/terven/Furby.html About the church ruin in Furby] *[http://biphome.spray.se/badelunda/Karta.htm A map of Badelunda parish] {{coord|59|38|N|16|41|E|region:SE_type:city_source:GNS-enwiki|display=title}} [[Category:Populated places in Västmanland County]]
